when plug in a USB, the device driver in kernal generates a uevent which is then sent to user-space device manager daemon called udev, then udev creates a device node in /dev.

Dmesg is a tool to display messages from ring buffer in kernal.
$ dmesg

udevadm is a management tool for udev.
$ udevadm monitor                            //detects uevents

$ lspci
$ lsblk
$ lscpu
$ lsmem --summary
$ free -m                                    //total memory vs used memory
$ sudo lshw                                  //lshw shows hardware configuration
